node.text:
We would like to present to you the @JacobAndCo Mistery Tourbillon Rainbow! This timepiece is something from the gods! The rainbow shine soo bright that is capable of blind your eyes! Truely a master piece! All handmade! Awesome! Unique!

Mystery dials, timepieces where the indicators seem to be floating over the dial, are part of the grand history of watchmaking, going back about 200 years when it was first invented by a clockmaker who was also a practicing magician and illusionist. Jacob & Co. has brought the mystery back with an innovative, contemporary high watchmaking and high jewelry twist.

The Mystery Tourbillon Rainbow combines high watchmaking; a world first with two linked central, back-to-back triple axis tourbillons; and high jewelry craftsmanship, with a rose gold case paved with multicolored sapphires. The sophisticated and ground-breaking Mystery was more than one year in development.
